metadata.description:
The End Of Things


The temporal space is a heap of badly arranged boxes.
If everything disappears. What is left?
Do you exist?
Your skin, my pain, my mourning, my joys, my laughter, 
Lost forever in a memory of your own.

Virtual memory of an ideal reality.
Which is only in power.
The act has abandoned.
Nothing lasts.

The famous needle. The ultimate limit. 
Reaper of my decision. 
Abrupt end to my courage. 

The madness is to believe that it will change by repeating the same thing every day. 

Not even this pixel is eternal.
I am 2.54 centimeters away from my happiness,
Immaterial but not abstract.
Too far, so close, or already gone,
The possible looks like the real,
It just lacks existence.

INFORMATIONS : 

Edition : 01/01 - Unique

Nft created from the photographic series 'The End on Things' visible on my website www.marinefoissey.com
